# email_amns package

STEPS TO SEND MAIL :
  from email_amns import PublishMail

  mail_status=PublishMail(mail_subject='THIS IS MAIL PACKAGE TEST 1', mail_content='THIS IS MAIL PACKAGE TEST 1',
            to='abc1@mail.co.in,abc2@mail.co.in,',cc='abc3@mail.co.in,abc4@mail.co.in,',
            bcc='abc5@mail.co.in,abc6@mail.co.in,',sender_alias='abc',sender_email='abc7@mail.co.in',
           sender_password='abc@123',attchment_paths=['E:/TUTORIALs/filename1.pdf','E:/TUTORIALs/filename2.pdf']
           ,mailserver='email.smtp.com',rcpt_options=['NOTIFY=SUCCESS,DELAY,FAILURE'])

  print(mail_status[0])

About Parameters :

  mail_subject ={NOT COMPULSORY} subject of your mail
  mail_content ={NOT COMPULSORY} mail body (may content html syntax)
  to ={REQUIRED} list of mail ids of receiver (@eg. 'abc1@mail.co.in,abc2@mail.co.in,')
  cc ={NOT COMPULSORY} list of mail ids in cc of receiver (@eg. 'abc3@mail.co.in,abc4@mail.co.in,')
  bcc ={NOT COMPULSORY} list of mail ids in bcc of receiver (@eg. 'abc5@mail.co.in,abc6@mail.co.in,')
  sender_alias ={REQUIRED} Login alias of sender (@eg. sdds)
  sender_email ={REQUIRED} Login email id of sender (@eg. sdds@mail.co.in)
  sender_password ={REQUIRED} Login password of sender (@eg. ******)
  attchment_paths ={NOT COMPULSORY} list of path of attachment files
  mailserver ={REQUIRED} mail server from which mail will be send (@eg. email.stmp.com)
  mailserverport ={NOT REQUIRED} If nothing is given, default port 25 will be used.
  auth_protocol ={NOT REQUIRED} If nothing is given, 'SMTP-AUTH' protocol will be used.
  auth ={NOT REQUIRED} Default is True, if authentication is not required, pass False.
  is_file ={NOT REQUIRED} Default is False, if sending attachments in a mail, if files are given as object then argument must be True.
  file_object_list ={NOT REQUIRED} if is_file is True, then this parameter must contain the file objects.
  rcpt_options ={NOT REQUIRED} get status of delivered mail

Return variables:

To: Receipients wo were in TO when sending mail 
Cc: Receipients wo were in CC when sending mail
Bcc: Receipients wo were in BCC when sending mail
Subject: Subject of the Mail
smtp_response: Response received from SMTP Relay for the Mail (Success: Empty Dictionary, Failure: Error messages)


